data.value: This form allows you to create many users at once either from an uploaded or local text file. Each line in the file specifies one user in the following format :

data.name: many_descafter

data.name: batch_desc
data.value: This form allows you to create, modify or delete many users at once from an uploaded or local text file. Each line in the file specifies one action to take, depending on its first field. The line formats are :

data.name: batch_descafter
data.value: In create lines, if the uid field is left empty, Webmin will assign a UID automatically. If the gid field is empty, Webmin will create a new group with the same name as the user. The username, homedir and shell fields must be supplied for every user - all other fields are allowed to be empty. If the passwd field is blank, no password will be assigned for the user. If it contains just the letter x, the account will be locked. Otherwise, the text in the field will be taken as the cleartext password and encrypted.

data.name: batch_descafter2
data.value: In modify lines, an empty field will be taken to mean that the corresponding user attribute is not to be modified.
